PrimaryInformation.Description: Ideal for medium-heavy duty applications with state-of-the-art features and industry leading power.
PrimaryInformation.ExtendedDescription: The Heavy Lift HL2040R truck delivers maximum performance for medium to heavy-duty applications with state-of-the art features and industry leading power. MZDA 2.0L engine offers high performance with outstanding operating costs. The truck's lateral stability has a simple, maintenance-free design that does not compromise when operating on uneven surface travel. Operator comfort is enhanced by the increased foot space in the well designed operator's compartment. The isolated powertrain reduces noise and vibration minimizing operator fatigue and increasing operator productivity throughout a shift. From the rear-opening, one-piece hood and on board diagnostics, to the reliable, most comprehensive parts availability in the industry, this truck was designed with service details in mind.

PrimaryInformation.Description: The HL2020R has the ergonomic comfort and the specifications you need.
PrimaryInformation.ExtendedDescription: The Reach X-Narrow 16W excels in situations that require operator order selecting, picking and handling of various items in multi-level, narrow aisle applications. The truck features 24-volt power, state-of-the-art technology with infinitely variable travel and lift speeds, excellent visibility, ergonomic controls and operator comfort. Controller Area Network (CANbus) communications and Separately Excited Motor (SEM) control technology streamlines system communications. This reduces wiring and component complexity and eases serviceability. Smart-Glide™ is offered as standard equipment for step-less speed control by optimizing the maximum travel speed at various fork heights.

PrimaryInformation.Description: The Pneumatic Tire Truck is designed and manufactured the most demanding applications.
PrimaryInformation.ExtendedDescription: HeavyLift Pneumatic Lift Trucks are designed and manufactured for some of the most demanding industries and applications. The HeavyLift Pneumatic Tire DB5 uses a rugged 6 cylinder MZDA, GEM, or Cumulus engines in gasoline, LPG and Diesel. These engines are application proven for performance and reliability. HeavyLift Techtronix electronically controlled transmissions offer superior performance & durability. HeavyLift masts incorporate innovative engineering for excellent visibility and solid construction. All components are engineered for outstanding performance and extended, low-maintenance life.

PrimaryInformation.Description: Gem V4 Dual Fuel systen 2.5 liter engine
PrimaryInformation.ExtendedDescription: The GEM LP engines use sequential port fuel injection. The GEM LP engines use a vaporizer/ regulator to convert the fuel from a liquid to a gas for vapor injection. The Engine Control Unit electronically controls the fuel, air, and spark advance to provide the necessary torque. The engine control unit’s inputs include manifold air pressure, manifold air temperature, engine coolant temperature, accelerator pedal position, throttle position, engine speed, cam signal, and oxygen sensor signal.
